docs.abstract: Representative Katie Porter is one of the first to endorse impeachment proceedings among House Democrats who are expected to face tough re-election campaigns.
docs.snippet: Representative Katie Porter is one of the first to endorse impeachment proceedings among House Democrats who are expected to face tough re-election campaigns.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Katie Porter, a law professor who narrowly flipped part of Republicans’ Southern California stronghold to the Democrats in last year’s midterm elections, said on Monday that she would support opening an impeachment inquiry into President Trump.

headline.main: Democrat in Competitive California District Joins Call for Impeachment Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Vulnerable Democrat Calls For Impeachment Inquiry

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos and Julie Hirschfeld Davis

docs.abstract: Talk of purported Iran-Qaeda ties is raising questions about whether the Trump administration is laying the groundwork to claim that it needs no new legal authority to take military action.
docs.snippet: Talk of purported Iran-Qaeda ties is raising questions about whether the Trump administration is laying the groundwork to claim that it needs no new legal authority to take military action.
docs.lead_paragraph: In public remarks and classified briefings, Trump administration officials keep emphasizing purported ties between Iran and Al Qaeda. Some lawmakers suspect that the executive branch is toying with claiming that it already has congressional authorization to attack Iran based on the nearly 18-year-old law approving a war over the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks.

headline.main: Could Trump Use the Sept. 11 War Law to Attack Iran Without Going to Congress?
headline.print_headline: Could Trump Use 9/11 War Law to Bypass Congress and Attack Iran?

docs.abstract: Stephanie Grisham, currently the spokeswoman for the first lady, Melania Trump, is one of those under consideration to succeed Sarah Huckabee Sanders.
docs.snippet: Stephanie Grisham, currently the spokeswoman for the first lady, Melania Trump, is one of those under consideration to succeed Sarah Huckabee Sanders.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Sarah Huckabee Sanders’s announcement that she would step down as White House press secretary has set off the latest round of musical chairs in the West Wing and an internal debate over whether to revive the daily news briefing as President Trump heads into the thick of election season.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic-led House Intelligence Committee said on Thursday that it had issued two new subpoenas demanding that Michael T. docs.abstract: President Trump hosted President Andrzej Duda of Poland with an elaborate show of support, including an F-35 that roared over the White House.
docs.snippet: President Trump hosted President Andrzej Duda of Poland with an elaborate show of support, including an F-35 that roared over the White House.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump welcomed Poland’s nationalist president to the White House on Wednesday with an elaborate show of support, promising more American troops, defending Warsaw’s record on democracy and staging a rare and showy F-35 jet flyover to mark their friendship.

headline.main: Trump Embraces Poland’s President and Promises Him More U.S. Troops
headline.print_headline: Polish Leader’s Warm Welcome Comes With a Military Flourish

docs.abstract: Donald J. Trump carried several key states on a vow to end manufacturing job losses. That has not happened.
docs.snippet: Donald J. Trump carried several key states on a vow to end manufacturing job losses. That has not happened.
docs.lead_paragraph: DIMONDALE, Mich. — In August 2016, Donald J. Trump was full of promises when he spoke to a packed crowd at the Summit Sports and Ice Complex here. Predicting that he would carry Michigan, a state that had not voted for a Republican presidential candidate since 1988, Mr. Trump said his would be “a victory for the wage-earner, the factory worker, a victory for the everyday citizen.”

headline.main: Trump Promised a Manufacturing Renaissance. What Happens in 2020 in Places That Lost Those Jobs?
headline.print_headline: Rethinking Trump Where Factory Jobs Fell

docs.abstract: The newly released testimony by the Commerce Department’s counsel gave ammunition to Democrats who have accused the Trump administration of trying to skew census results to Republicans’ benefit.
docs.snippet: The newly released testimony by the Commerce Department’s counsel gave ammunition to Democrats who have accused the Trump administration of trying to skew census results to Republicans’ benefit.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Commerce Department official considering whether the 2020 census should include a citizenship question told congressional aides that he consulted with a professor who argued that the addition was necessary to exclude undocumented immigrants from a redistricting of House seats, testimony released on Tuesday shows.

headline.main: Official’s Testimony Adds to Rancor Around Census Citizenship Question
